{"trip_id":"2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees","epigraph":{"quote":"I sat on a terrace + watched forked lightening strike the mountains in the distance. Sparks seemed to fly where the forks hit the rock."},"moments":[{"seq":2,"place_id":"portsmouth-uk","lon":-1.0906023,"lat":50.800031,"place":"Portsmouth, UK","date":"2004-07-31","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"We left at 6 for the ferry.","images":[]},{"seq":3,"place_id":"bilbao-spain","lon":-2.9350039,"lat":43.2630018,"place":"Bilbao, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"It's amazing looking - titanium + limestone. We walked round the outside in the drizzle.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0022_L_1.webp","w":900,"h":822,"caption":"The beach at Motrika","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":4,"place_id":"guernica-gernika-lumo-spain","lon":-2.6800756,"lat":43.3155336,"place":"Guernica (Gernika-Lumo), Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"We had salad + escalope + tuna/sword fish + cold rice pudding - very good.","images":[]},{"seq":5,"place_id":"mutriku-spain","lon":-2.3871098,"lat":43.3071181,"place":"Mutriku, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"We drove on + found a campsite on the east side of Mutriku, above the harbour.","images":[]},{"seq":6,"place_id":"san-sebastian-donostia-spain","lon":-1.9769301,"lat":43.3177368,"place":"San Sebastian (Donostia), Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"transit_stop","quote":"Donostia-San Sebastian, then south Towards Pamplona.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0023_L_1.webp","w":881,"h":900,"caption":"East side of Getaria - the harbour. Our campsite is at X","type":"photo"}]},{"seq":7,"place_id":"puente-la-reina-navarre-spain","lon":-1.8123198,"lat":42.6914331,"place":"Puente la Reina, Navarre, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"We had lunch at Puente de la Reina, which has a lovely old bridge. Simon had pale green beans.","images":[]},{"seq":8,"place_id":"santa-maria-de-eunate-navarre-spain","lon":-1.761504,"lat":42.6722283,"place":"Santa Maria de Eunate, Navarre, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"It was in a field of sunflowers.","images":[]},{"seq":9,"place_id":"lumbier-navarre-spain","lon":-1.3083408,"lat":42.6522082,"place":"Lumbier, Navarre, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"The cool swimming was marvellous","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0023_R_1.webp","w":900,"h":668,"caption":"Aitreta Campsite","type":"photo"}]},{"seq":10,"place_id":"foz-de-lumbier-navarre-spain","lon":-1.3018021,"lat":42.6322043,"place":"Foz de Lumbier, Navarre, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"There are buzzards cirding at the top of diff + storks nests on the churches.","images":[]},{"seq":11,"place_id":"monasterio-de-san-salvador-de-leyre-navarre-spain","lon":-1.1708621,"lat":42.6363204,"place":"Monasterio de San Salvador de Leyre, Navarre, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"the church, with a lovely doorway into a chapel, + the Judgement portal with Jonah + the Whale.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0024_L_1.webp","w":593,"h":596,"caption":"EuNATE","type":"postcard"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0024_L_2.webp","w":593,"h":628,"caption":"LuMBIER","type":"postcard"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0024_R_1.webp","w":618,"h":596,"caption":"Gorge of Lumbier","type":"photo"}]},{"seq":13,"place_id":"ruesta-aragon-spain","lon":-1.0761589,"lat":42.5888182,"place":"Ruesta, Aragon, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"Simon weeded one of the yellow arrows on the track by our campsite because pilgrims were missing it.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0025_R_1.webp","w":830,"h":403,"caption":"outline sketch of lake or campsite terrain","type":"sketch"}]},{"seq":14,"place_id":"jaca-aragon-spain","lon":-0.5493763,"lat":42.5692878,"place":"Jaca, Aragon, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"our best meal in Spain - a glass of gazpacho, cold meats... & liver & chips, then chocolate mousse for pud. Then excellent coffee.","images":[]},{"seq":15,"place_id":"ainsa-aragon-spain","lon":0.1386444,"lat":42.4171898,"place":"Ainsa, Aragon, Spain","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"It has been marvellous swimming in the heat & washing my hair in a warm shower afterwards.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0027_L_1.webp","w":591,"h":338,"caption":"wooden texture close-up","type":"photo"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0027_L_2.webp","w":579,"h":338,"caption":"doorway with cow or animal","type":"photo"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0027_L_3.webp","w":591,"h":354,"caption":"stone wall with small window","type":"photo"}]},{"seq":17,"place_id":"massat-ariege-france","lon":1.3480455,"lat":42.8888745,"place":"Massat, Ariege, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"Walking around the village after supper was nice. Good views of a mountain valley.","images":[]},{"seq":18,"place_id":"bedeilhac-cave-grotte-de-bedeilhac-ariege-france","lon":1.5674969,"lat":42.8816132,"place":"Bedeilhac Cave (Grotte de Bedeilhac), Ariege, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"It is so big that an aeroplane flew out of it. During the war the Germans built an aeroplane factory in it.","images":[]},{"seq":19,"place_id":"tarascon-sur-ariege-france","lon":1.6043495,"lat":42.8492109,"place":"Tarascon-sur-Ariege, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"we drove on to a Park of Prehistory, which we very much enjoyed.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0032_L_1.webp","w":631,"h":900,"caption":"Copies of Niaux Cave paintings, Salon Noir Bisons, Tarascon sur Ariège","type":"photo"}]},{"seq":20,"place_id":"ax-les-thermes-ariege-france","lon":1.83784,"lat":42.7193011,"place":"Ax-les-Thermes, Ariege, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"Last night John beat Eve at scrabble with Clippers over a red - 83 points.","images":[]},{"seq":21,"place_id":"montaillou-ariege-france","lon":1.8974651,"lat":42.7869501,"place":"Montaillou, Ariege, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"The Cathars Bookshop was closed.","images":[]},{"seq":22,"place_id":"col-de-jau-pyrenees-orientales-france","lon":2.250713,"lat":42.6879129,"place":"Col de Jau, Pyrenees-Orientales, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"transit_stop","quote":"5 very naughty horses terrorising car drivers for bread!!","images":[]},{"seq":23,"place_id":"prades-pyrenees-orientales-france","lon":2.4230925,"lat":42.6181232,"place":"Prades, Pyrenees-Orientales, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"Then we reached Prades. The Municipal Camping was complet.","images":[]},{"seq":25,"place_id":"vernet-les-bains-pyrenees-orientales-france","lon":2.3878706,"lat":42.5484832,"place":"Vernet-les-Bains, Pyrenees-Orientales, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"We had a lovely relaxed day at this campsite, which is one of the nicest we have ever been to.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0034_R_1.webp","w":900,"h":708,"caption":"Les Pyrénées-Orientales — Vernet-les-Bains, Choeur de Bain","type":"postcard"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0036_L_1.webp","w":848,"h":900,"caption":"Saint-Martin du Canigou","type":"postcard"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0036_R_1.webp","w":866,"h":900,"caption":"ABBAYE SAINT-MARTIN-DU-CANIGOU","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":26,"place_id":"eus-pyrenees-orientales-france","lon":2.457582,"lat":42.644353,"place":"Eus, Pyrenees-Orientales, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"The students could communicate so well, inspite of speaking different languages.","images":[]},{"seq":27,"place_id":"ille-sur-tet-pyrenees-orientales-france","lon":2.6224853,"lat":42.6709665,"place":"Ille-sur-Tet, Pyrenees-Orientales, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"transit_stop","quote":"We ended up watching our pizzas being made at Ille-sur-Tet.","images":[]},{"seq":28,"place_id":"trebes-aude-france","lon":2.4412579,"lat":43.2108325,"place":"Trebes, Aude, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"The washing dried incredibly quickly at Trebe.","images":[]},{"seq":29,"place_id":"carcassonne-aude-france","lon":2.3491069,"lat":43.2130358,"place":"Carcassonne, Aude, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"Gorgeous shops & I bought a 3m. tablecloth with blue grapes.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0039_R_1.webp","w":870,"h":900,"caption":"Carcassonne, Aude","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":30,"place_id":"realmont-tarn-france","lon":2.1889958,"lat":43.7760912,"place":"Realmont, Tarn, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"Charles bought croissants, pain au chocolat, baguettes & an apple pie to die for. We breakfasted in a lay-by.","images":[]},{"seq":31,"place_id":"albi-tarn-france","lon":2.147899,"lat":43.9277552,"place":"Albi, Tarn, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"The carvings are magnificent — Burgundian influence in heavy folds, very expressive faces & hands — Job's sad face & Judith's red dress.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0040_R_1.webp","w":811,"h":900,"caption":"St. Cecily (B) Albi Cathedral.","type":"postcard"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0041_L_1.webp","w":900,"h":755,"caption":"Gardens of Archbishop's palace, Albi, above R. Tarn","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":32,"place_id":"eymoutiers-haute-vienne-france","lon":1.7432748,"lat":45.7389214,"place":"Eymoutiers, Haute-Vienne, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"It's very disappointing that, having wanted to swim for days & being much too hot, it rained in the night.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0042_L_1.webp","w":820,"h":900,"caption":"Musée Toulouse-Lautrec, Albi","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":33,"place_id":"futuroscope-poitiers-chasseneuil-du-poitou-france","lon":0.3773648,"lat":46.6699758,"place":"Futuroscope, Poitiers (Chasseneuil-du-Poitou), France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"John knew the hotel was OK because there was a porsche boxster outside","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0042_R_1.webp","w":566,"h":483,"caption":"Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec par lui-même, 1896","type":"postcard"},{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0043_L_1.webp","w":519,"h":451,"caption":"PAVE de CHEVRE Lou Mountognol cheese label","type":"ticket"}]},{"seq":34,"place_id":"le-mans-france","lon":0.1967849,"lat":48.0073849,"place":"Le Mans, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"transit_stop","quote":"We drove north, stopping for food... We drove past Le Mans.","images":[]},{"seq":35,"place_id":"rouvrou-suisse-normande-orne-france","lon":-0.399265,"lat":48.8420556,"place":"Rouvrou, Suisse Normande, Orne, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"At 5.45 we arrived at Rouvrou in the Le Suisse Normand. Simon remember where it was.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0044_L_1.webp","w":767,"h":900,"caption":"Les Chemins de la Liberté / The Paths to Freedom","type":"postcard"}]},{"seq":36,"place_id":"pegasus-bridge-benouville-normandy-france","lon":-0.2741164,"lat":49.2423811,"place":"Pegasus Bridge (Benouville), Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"The Bailey Bridge was taken down in 1946 + used as a bridge for a local town over their river for 50 years.","images":[]},{"seq":37,"place_id":"arromanches-les-bains-normandy-france","lon":-0.6227946,"lat":49.3372557,"place":"Arromanches-les-Bains, Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"looked at the circular movie of the invasion + remains. Then had an ice cream.","images":[]},{"seq":38,"place_id":"bayeux-normandy-france","lon":-0.7024738,"lat":49.2764624,"place":"Bayeux, Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"it hailed pine cones on top of the van.","images":[]},{"seq":39,"place_id":"port-en-bessin-huppain-normandy-france","lon":-0.7526611,"lat":49.3458498,"place":"Port-en-Bessin-Huppain, Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"We stopped at Port en Bessin to buy John's birthday cake.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0045_L_1.webp","w":900,"h":688,"caption":"Bayeux Tapestry scene, feast table","type":"photo"}]},{"seq":40,"place_id":"longues-sur-mer-normandy-france","lon":-0.6976428,"lat":49.3357159,"place":"Longues-sur-Mer, Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"It could see all the way from Cherbourg almost to Pegasus Bridge, but no radar.","images":[]},{"seq":41,"place_id":"pointe-du-hoc-normandy-france","lon":-0.9894089,"lat":49.3978217,"place":"Pointe du Hoc, Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"main_stop","quote":"the land around is scrubby & barren, so farmers haven't put the soil together to farm again.","images":[]},{"seq":42,"place_id":"barfleur-normandy-france","lon":-1.2644272,"lat":49.6706815,"place":"Barfleur, Normandy, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"overnight_base","quote":"We had a delicious supper to mark John's birthday. Iles flottant.","images":[]},{"seq":43,"place_id":"cherbourg-france","lon":-1.6249565,"lat":49.6425343,"place":"Cherbourg, France","date":"2004-07-31","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"glorious sunshine, tide coming in, but so are purply grey clouds.","images":[]},{"seq":44,"place_id":"portsmouth-uk","lon":-1.0906023,"lat":50.800031,"place":"Portsmouth, UK","date":"2004-07-31","role":"crossing_terminal","quote":"We finally reached home at 7. Thomas + Peter were there.","images":[{"src":"media/2004-spain-bilbao-basque-coast-aragon-pyrenees/B_0047_L_1.webp","w":900,"h":613,"caption":"BARFLEUR","type":"postcard"}]}]}